Class WorkspaceComparisonFlags

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.team.scm.common.WorkspaceComparisonFlags

  • public class WorkspaceComparisonFlags
extends java.lang.Object
    Flags used to describe different variations of workspace comparison.

        Constant Field Values

      • INCLUDE_BASELINE_INFO

        public static final int INCLUDE_BASELINE_INFO
        Compare workspaces with respect to baselines. Empty baselines are not included by default. An empty baseline is defined as follows: - does not contain change sets as compared to the predecessor baseline - does not contain change sets unique to the other workspace being compared. - is not the basis for a workspace involved in the comparison
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • INCLUDE_EMPTY_BASELINES

        public static final int INCLUDE_EMPTY_BASELINES
        Include empty baselines in findings. It is illegal to use this bit mask without INCLUDE_BASELINE_INFO.
        See Also:

      • CALCULATE_UPDATES_FOR_POTENTIAL_CONFLICTS_ONLY

        public static final int CALCULATE_UPDATES_FOR_POTENTIAL_CONFLICTS_ONLY
        When calling the IScmService#compareWorkspaces(IWorkspaceHandle, IWorkspaceHandle, com.ibm.team.scm.common.internal.dto.RemoteRepoDescriptor, int, IComponentHandle[], com.ibm.team.scm.common.dto.ISynchronizationTimes[], IRepositoryProgressMonitor) method, only calculate the update information if there is a potential for conflicts. That is, the IUpdateReport.updates() and IUpdateReport.conflicts() will only be calculated if there are incoming and outgoing change sets.
        See Also:

        Constant Field Values

      • INCLUDE_CHANGESET_SOURCE_LINK_INFO

        public static final int INCLUDE_CHANGESET_SOURCE_LINK_INFO
        Its possible that of the incoming/outgoing change sets that some of them may be logically in the other change history because there is a change set in the change history with the same original source id. If this information is to be be calculated and included in the report, set the flag when comparing workspaces.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CALCULATE_UPDATES_FOR_STREAM_COMPARE

        public static final int CALCULATE_UPDATES_FOR_STREAM_COMPARE
        By default, an update report is not calculated when the local workspace is a stream. Passing this flag will cause an update report to potentially be included, depending on the other flags passed.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • INVERT_COMPONENT_FILTER

        public static final int INVERT_COMPONENT_FILTER
        Invert the default component filter behavior. If the default behavior is to exclude the specified components, then this flag will cause them to be included and all other components to be excluded. May not be supported on all api calls
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CALCULATE_ACCURATE_BEFORE_STATES

        public static final int CALCULATE_ACCURATE_BEFORE_STATES
        When comparing configurations, the result will always include accurate current states for any updates returned. However, by default, the previous states may not be accurate in some corner cases such as those involving conflicts or branches that contain the same end state. This flag can be specified to indicate that the previous states need to be accurate as well. May not be supported on all api calls.
        See Also:
        IScmService.compareConfigurations(com.ibm.team.scm.common.internal.dto.ServiceConfigurationProvider, com.ibm.team.scm.common.internal.dto.ServiceConfigurationProvider, com.ibm.team.scm.common.internal.dto.RemoteRepoDescriptor, int, com.ibm.team.scm.common.dto.ISynchronizationTimes[], IRepositoryProgressMonitorHandle), IScmService.compareHistoryConfigurations(IHistoryReference, IHistoryReference, com.ibm.team.scm.common.internal.dto.RemoteRepoDescriptor, int, IComponentHandle[], com.ibm.team.scm.common.dto.ISynchronizationTimes[], IRepositoryProgressMonitorHandle), Constant Field Values
